<parameter name="old_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-35',
    prompt: 'Schedule and complete a comprehensive relationship "first month review" meeting to evaluate how your partnership is developing and address any early concerns',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Conducting a formal review of your relationship\'s first month helps identify patterns, celebrate what\'s working well, and address any concerns before they become larger issues. Set aside 2-3 hours in a comfortable, private setting to discuss your individual experiences, communication successes and challenges, physical and emotional intimacy levels, and any adjustments needed for your second month together. This proactive check-in demonstrates your commitment to intentional relationship building and creates a foundation for regular relationship maintenance that strengthens your partnership over time.'
  }</parameter>
<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-35',
    prompt: 'Schedule and complete a comprehensive relationship "first month review" meeting to evaluate how your partnership is developing and address any early concerns',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Conducting a formal review of your relationship\'s first month helps identify patterns, celebrate what\'s working well, and address any concerns before they become larger issues. Set aside 2-3 hours in a comfortable, private setting to discuss your individual experiences, communication successes and challenges, physical and emotional intimacy levels, and any adjustments needed for your second month together. This proactive check-in demonstrates your commitment to intentional relationship building and creates a foundation for regular relationship maintenance that strengthens your partnership over time.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-36',
    prompt: 'Research and practice conflict de-escalation techniques by role-playing potential disagreement scenarios and learning healthy response strategies',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Learning how to calm tensions during conflicts is essential for maintaining respect and finding solutions when disagreements arise in your relationship. Research evidence-based de-escalation techniques like taking calming breaths, using "I" statements, and recognizing emotional triggers, then practice these skills by role-playing common relationship scenarios with your partner. This proactive skill-building helps you both respond thoughtfully rather than reactively during real conflicts, creating a foundation of emotional safety that strengthens your partnership.'
  }</parameter>
</invoke>
